cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "LLM Pre-Send Leakage Benchmark"
message: "If you use this benchmark in your research or work, please cite it as below."
type: dataset
authors:
  - given-names: Bikram
    family-names: Vikash
    affiliation: Aegis Preflight
    website: "https://aegispreflight.com"
repository-code: "https://github.com/aegis-preflight/llm-pre-send-leakage-benchmark"
url: "https://github.com/aegis-preflight/llm-pre-send-leakage-benchmark"
abstract: >-
  An empirical benchmark of pre-send PII, secret, and PHI leakage across
  20 popular AI tools. Measures what data leaves the user's device before
  reaching the underlying model. Includes a synthesized 100-prompt test
  corpus (Faker-generated, seeded, no real PII), a reproducible test harness
  for API-direct and web-based tools, and per-tool scoring on a five-dimension
  rubric covering pre-send redaction, user notification, transit encryption,
  vendor retention TOS, and audit log accessibility. Maps to OWASP LLM06
  (Sensitive Information Disclosure).
keywords:
  - LLM
  - large-language-model
  - AI-security
  - data-leakage
  - PII
  - PHI
  - OWASP-LLM06
  - benchmark
  - pre-send
  - data-loss-prevention
  - AI-DLP
